            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Isaac Ostland</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="ostlandI" start="1113.684" end="x">There we spent two years. We went through [he apparently corrects himself] three years time and we went through all the hardships which the Russian people went through, especially the evacuees, which was still harder for religious people. Still I was able to observe dietary laws, the Sabbath, and all the Jewish laws; naturally with great, great difficulties. Very rarely were there people who could stick it out. In the year 44 . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="1145.609" end="x">Now, in these three years, what were you doing? Did you report to the Russians for work?</span>
