            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Isaac Ostland</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="ostlandI" start="1197.239" end="x">Together with Christians.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="1198.721" end="x">And how did they behave towards you?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Isaac Ostland</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="ostlandI" start="1200.987" end="x">Being there the only Jew, perfectly strange and unfamiliar to them, and being a deeply religious Jew which they haven't seen already for 25 years, they developed towards me a relationship as to a stranger who has nothing in common with them. They could not understand me, they could not comprehend [my behavior], they knew that here was a stranger with whom they have nothing in common. I did not suffer from anti-Semitism, except, naturally, the young ones bothered me somewhat. But the old ones . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="boderD" start="1231.190" end="x">Did you keep your beard?</span>
